=Description=

Juan Arellano:

"Bogotá, like other Latin American cities, has spaces for technological activists and those who want to learn about technology to meet and generate new synergies and activities where they develop practical applications for these issues. Fundación Casa del Bosque [es] is one of these spaces.

The Foundation, formed by an interdisciplinary team, provides management training in web technologies, 3D animation, computer security and programming languages, and also carries out research about the social digital divide, public technological debt, technopolitics, activism and technology in digital literacy in Colombia."
(http://rising.globalvoicesonline.org/blog/2014/05/02/casa-del-bosque-foundation-technopolitics-and-activism-in-bogota/)

